EmailTemplate.subject: Invitation: Special Screening of Miss Representation with Guest Speaker Melinda Tankard Reist
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Lead.FirstName}
St Andrew’s would like to invite students, parents, friends and community members to a special screening of
Miss Representation followed by guest speaker Melinda Tankard Reist
The documentary film Miss Representation by Jennifer Siebel Newsom examines how women are ‘misrepresented’ in the media, where women are valued primarily for their looks and youth rather than their character, intelligence, achievements and substance. The film examines the role both genders and all ages play in reinforcing gender bias and stereotyping. Newsom’s motivation comes from the desire to create a better world for her own daughter. The language of the film is occasionally confronting and while the School does not endorse all views presented, it is a very timely and helpful illumination of the issues surrounding the portrayal of women in the media. - Grace Stone, Head of Senior College
Date: 7pm, 24 July 2014
Venue: BBC auditorium - 51 Druitt Street
Cost: Gold coin donation at the door
Please book online at: www.trybooking.com/FDOQ
For more information about the movie please visit: http://film.missrepresentation.org/
Melinda Tankard Reist is a Canberra author, speaker, media commentator, blogger and advocate for women and girls. She is well known for her work on the objectification of women and sexualisation of girls and efforts to address violence against women and is a co-founder of Collective Shout: for world free of sexploitation
Kind regards
Bruce Perry Registrar/Mathematics Teacher
